description: Your trusty laptop! Can't go anywhere without it.
name: Laptop Computer

description:
Just a plain T-shirt. This is what you always wear,
unlike Beck, who always wears a non-plain T-shirt.
name: Plain T-Shirt

description:
The book that Waliullah is currently reading. Honestly
an insane read. Those sentences...
name: Finnegans Wake

description:
A crown that he got from the Washington D.C. trip
during your sophomore year. Cheaply made, but it'll do.
name: Burger King Crown

description:
Juan's cell phone! You saw his Instagram reels once,
and you were never the same since.
name: Cell Phone

description:
The classic Juan trenchcoat. Wore it once and was
endlessly mocked. Evers thinks it looks good on him.
name: Trench Coat

description:
Daniel's trusty drawing notebook, where he jots down
all of his ideas, doodles, etc.
name: Drawing Notebook

description:
Just a regular blue sweater. Makes Daniel look like a
familiar RPG character...
name: Blue Sweater

description:
A comic featuring one of Will's characters, Sunny the
Sunflower! This town ain't big enough for the two of us.
name: Sunny Comic

description:
Will's headphones. Always playing a catchy tune from
his current videogame hyperfixation.
name: Headphones

description:
The build that Adrianna and Waliullah made inside their
Project Design class. Sturdy, yet flexible.
name: Project Design Build

description:
Adrianna's hoodie. Whenever it's cold outside, she has
this on hand!
name: Hoodie

description:
Journal 3(?) from Gravity Falls. You're not sure how
Beck got this, but it's pretty cool.
name: Gravity Falls Journal

description:
Beck never wears just a plain T-shirt. It always has
some kind of design on it. Despicable.
name: Non-Plain T-Shirt

description:
From "Total Hunger Drama Games Island", the safety
statue given to Team 3... It's just the number 3.
name: Team 3 Safety Statue

description:
Sturdy armor from Hylics, one of Will Dwyer's favorite
games. Does the job.
name: Hylics Armor

description:
Allen describes it as "a pendant that's made of a cool
rock." Important to him, but why..?
name: Rock Pendant

description:
Allen always carries this around. He says it brings
extra luck, but you're not convinced.
name: 4-Leaf Clover Bracelet

description:
Aubree's sketchbook. More intricate drawings in here
(usually) than Daniel's notebook.
name: Sketchbook

description:
One of the many "fits" that Aubree wears. You never
see her without something fashionable on.
name: Fashion Outfit

description:
Josh's guitar, one of his many hobbies outside of
gaming. He plays it pretty well.
name: Bass Guitar

description:
Josh's backpack. Has a wide variety of stuff, such as
Band-aids, a Syringe, and Stuffed Mushrooms.
name: Backpack

description:
One of your old textbooks. You think this is Calculus?
You don't really remember, nor does it matter anymore.
name: Dusty Textbook

description:
Once belonged to the Fancy Rat. Eww. You almost don't
want to keep this, let alone wear it.
name: Fancy Hat

description:
An unusually large leaf. Although it is a leaf, it
has good defense!
name: Giant Leaf

description:
One of Mr. Pardee's diagrams. Infamously indecipherable
by almost all of his Chemistry students.
name: Diagram

description:
The #1 rule of Chemistry labs: never begin before
putting on your safety goggles!
name: Safety Goggles

description:
You see this and the rage begins to build up. Many of
your Chem labs had these very very annoying filters.
name: Lab Filter

description:
When working with more advanced chemicals, protection
is important. Wearer is immune to poison.
name: Safety Apron

description:
Awww, it's a little plush of Pusheen The Cat. Just
knowing Pusheen will protect you gives you hope.
name: Pusheen Plush

description:
A shirt with Pusheen The Cat's face on it. Abrupt, but
anyone who wears it is instantly more popular (def).
name: Pusheen Shirt

description:
A very important piece of technology, given by none
other than Mr. Lasecki. Immune to dumbing effects.
name: IT Mainframe

description:
In this heat, you'll take any coolness you can get.
Wearer can use one-use skills more than once.
name: Handheld Fan
